<div id="review_3386483087" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3386483087" />
    <a title="Baba" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60866073-baba"><img alt="Baba" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532961539p2/60866073.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3386483087?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Baba" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Baba" href="/user/show/60866073-baba">Baba</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330520331" href="/book/show/21066953-the-forgotten">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/60866073-baba?shelf=thrills-spills-kills-oh-my">thrills-spills-kills-oh-my</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3386483087" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17297631969289594628">John Puller is back, in this the second book in hi s series, he is in a town called called Paradise, where his aunt may have been unlawfully killed contrary to what was determined locally. His off-the-books and at times contrary investigation takes multiple turns and twists as it appears to feed into the notion of a wider conspiracy... but at the heart of the matter, what Puller wants is truth and justice for his dead relative. <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[This is a surprisingly informative and stark look at </span></span>
  <span id="freeText17297631969289594628" style="display:none">John Puller is back, in this the second book in hi s series, he is in a town called called Paradise, where his aunt may have been unlawfully killed contrary to what was determined locally. His off-the-books and at times contrary investigation takes multiple turns and twists as it appears to feed into the notion of a wider conspiracy... but at the heart of the matter, what Puller wants is truth and justice for his dead relative. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[This is a surprisingly informative and stark look at the new 'hot business' for organised crime - people trafficking.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>. This book is also blessed with a pretty rounded and interesting supporting cast. A book that takes a hard look at 'the forgotten' the (many) people who fall between the cracks, and whose wellbeing is of little real interest to most.<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1641492010i/32414511.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Mega best selling David Baldacci does have a bit more mettle in his pen than most of his equally super best selling peers, as his easy-read 'one or more protagonists investigate ever widening conspiracy usually started off with a murder' tales are not only very well plotted, they don't veer away from taking wider looks at America and the rest of the modern world. This thriller takes note of how women are (mis-)treated in the American military and police force; how America is reliant on immigrant labour; the way organised crime really works and more. 7 out of 12.<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1641492010i/32414512._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><b>2022 read, 2014 read</b></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></span>
  <a data-text-id="17297631969289594628" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


