  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2417368039" />
    <a title="Phrynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne"><img alt="Phrynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640891977p2/8655084.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2417368039?book_show_action=true">Feb 06, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phrynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phrynne" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne">Phrynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8655084-phrynne?shelf=3500-2022">3500-2022</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2417368039" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13479064294444089807">The second book in the John Puller series and it is much better that the first.<br/><br/>It is very easy to like Puller. Okay so he seems like a Jack Reacher clone, but Baldacci gives him a lot more character and, sensibly, allows him to look for other people to back him up in extreme situations. Not many people can expect a one star General as back up like Puller can! The book is action packed but there is a good story in there too and I really enjoyed watching the bad guys get their just desserts.<br/><br/>Puller</span>
  <span id="freeText13479064294444089807" style="display:none">The second book in the John Puller series and it is much better that the first.<br /><br />It is very easy to like Puller. Okay so he seems like a Jack Reacher clone, but Baldacci gives him a lot more character and, sensibly, allows him to look for other people to back him up in extreme situations. Not many people can expect a one star General as back up like Puller can! The book is action packed but there is a good story in there too and I really enjoyed watching the bad guys get their just desserts.<br /><br />Puller himself is a great character. He has a brother in prison and a father in residential care suffering from dementia, but he does not let this get him down. I enjoyed the way he dealt with his father by humouring him when his mind wanders. <br /><br />Altogether this was an excellent book and I have marked book three to read as soon as possible.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13479064294444089807" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


