  <span id="freeText2911006664178480149" style="display:none">3.5 stars...Nothing like a John Puller novel from way back when the series began.<br /><br />An unintentional re-read but still enjoyable even though it is out of sequence and so much more has happened to these characters. Baldacci writes a solid thriller.<br /><br />Gripping and full of commences there are subplots intertwined with the core story. I really enjoy Baldacci's writing style and attention to detail which makes the characters more realistic and engaging. His ability to have multiple storylines running simultaneously is masterful and keeps the reader entertained!. <br /><br />Yes, it is the standard arc for the genre but even a second time round it was enjoyable.</span>
